The biopsy demonstrates a well to moderately differentiated adenocarcinoma with glandular and tubular elements, mucin production, stromal desmoplasia and areas of necrosis.
The tumor cells are cuboidal to columnar with eosinophilic cytoplasm and prominent nucleoli and are positive for cytokeratin 7, DPC4 and CA19-9, with patchy positivity for HepPar-1 and arginase 1.
The differential diagnosis includes cholangiocarcinoma and less likely, pancreatic adenocarcinoma.
